Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.33,0:00:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll get back to these questions.\NSo you see, spiritual truth doesn't come out of historical cause and effectness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.85,0:00:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the downside of religion.\NIt's back there, and it's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.07,0:00:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The upside of religion is that it embodies\Nthe acknowledgement of holiness and sacredness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.94,0:00:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the respect for that which is sacred.\NThe one thing religion does get is the divinity of God
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.25,0:00:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sacredness of that divinity.\NThe great cathedrals of the world, which, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.14,0:00:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,right now we're calibrating a thousand things.\NShe's calibrating a thousand things.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.15,0:00:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm asking a thousand questions.\NAnyway, when you calibrate the great cathedrals of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.43,0:01:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they're high, 700s.\N700 is very, very unlikely as an occurrence in this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.51,0:01:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Few are the beings who ever even reach 700.\NBut the great cathedrals, Chartres,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.12,0:01:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the great cathedrals are stunning.\NWhen you walk into them, you're enveloped in this aura of sacredness,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.26,0:01:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,worship, devotion, and the energy of that prevails.\NIt's hard to be smart-ass in Chartres Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.28,0:01:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's hard in, I spoke one time in Westminster Abbey.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.56,0:01:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As you walk through Westminster Abbey,\Nthe great beings that have ever walked the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.35,0:02:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there's their tomb, there they lay there.\NI mean, as you walk across the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.84,0:02:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a plate there that tells you who's under there.\NYou think, my God, I shouldn't be stepping on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.20,0:02:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Shakespeare and here's Napoleon.\NAll these great beings, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.84,0:02:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord.\NAll right, so the great cathedrals.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.87,0:02:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the value of religion is it recognizes the sacredness of beauty.\NThe sacredness and the divinity of beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.93,0:02:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, beauty is one of the fastest ways to the sense of the presence of God.\NThat music that we just played is 700,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's almost impossible to function on that level.\NIn these lectures, I'm training myself to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.55,0:02:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to speak when you're weeping\Nbecause the beauty just wipes you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.59,0:03:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of divinity then is acknowledged\Nthrough the self-sacrifice of the thousands and thousands of workmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.43,0:03:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of those cathedrals took over a thousand years,\Na thousand years, and they're still working on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.18,0:03:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,An entire lifetime is devoted to carving this one pulpit.\NIt's in three dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.53,0:03:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's figures here and then figures...\NBehind those figures, then figures behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.03,0:03:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All done in hard wood.\NOne entire lifetime just to carve this one gift to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.96,0:03:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a gift.\NThe sense, the devotion of those whose devotion was so extreme
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.06,0:04:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,brings the energy of their devotion into your own inner experience,\Nand you get what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.09,0:04:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You get what it is.\NThe worship and the recognition and the acknowledgement of the sacredness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.53,0:04:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is.\NThat which is divine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.46,0:04:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a road which anyone can take.\NThe appreciation for beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.75,0:04:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A great aria in an opera can just wipe you out.\NWe're going to see Hansel and Gretel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The children's chorus from Hansel and Gretel wakes you out.\NLa Boheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.06,0:04:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an aria where he realizes that Mimi has just died,\Nand he screams Mimi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.98,0:04:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You break out crying every time you hear it.\NI've seen that opera 10 or 12, 15 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.18,0:04:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time.\NThe same.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.19,0:05:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The intensity of the love.\NWe experience the presence of God through love,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.04,0:05:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,through beauty,\Nthrough that which is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.04,0:05:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are worshipful,\Nand we respect the sacredness of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.83,0:05:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We worship God when we turn the black beetle over\Nfrom his back onto his tummy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.44,0:05:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so he can walk away,\Ninstead of living in the air with his legs wobbling in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.68,0:05:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that act, we worship God because\Nhe's a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.60,0:05:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a god.\NLife, so long as it exists in this form, is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.82,0:05:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize the sacredness.\NSo it's an act of worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.99,0:05:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All that we do that supports life\Nis a recognition of the respect for the sacredness of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.11,0:05:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's really all that's required.\NIs it possible to transform the physical body into a spiritual body?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.16,0:06:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, oh, it means as Jesus did.\NMy experience and understanding is,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.99,0:06:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as one goes out of body,\None's in the etheric body and the spiritual body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My guess would be that with the opening of the third eye,\Nthe disciples were able to witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.79,0:06:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,usually when somebody goes out of physicality into the etheric realm,\Nyou can't see them anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.79,0:06:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My guess would be that with the opening of the third spiritual eye,\Nthey witnessed the spirit body of the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.36,0:06:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask that.\NThe disciples did have the opening of the third eye
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.76,0:06:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and witnessed the etheric body.\NSo they merely saw the spirit leaving the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.87,0:07:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that the physical body is transformed into a spiritual body.\NIt's that the spiritual body which inhabits the physical body
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.13,0:07:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,during its physical life leaves it.\NSo it isn't like this physicality is transformed into the spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.97,0:07:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It just leaves it, is my understanding.\NCan kinesiology be used for future related questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.93,0:07:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NIt can't be used for the hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.27,0:07:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it can't be used for the future.\NThe reason is they're not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.48,0:07:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem with the hypothetical question is that\Nno answer is really possible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.99,0:07:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't exist in reality.\NWhat if mankind had four eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.91,0:07:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what would happen to them?\NThere's no answer to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.91,0:07:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypothetically,\Nthe hypothetical has no existence in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.91,0:07:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a nonsense question.\NA lot of politics is that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In which one quality is extracted\Nand then that's supposed to be the most important thing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.00,0:08:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,about your human being, you know.\NI got to do this for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.89,0:08:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Those people who talk from such ivory towers\Nshould travel the slums of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.89,0:08:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how much high pollutants\Nthe political ideology appeals to the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.98,0:08:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They're eating grubs to stay alive.\NAnd you want them to die for the vote?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.43,0:08:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Vote for what?\NThey're so far from that as a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.97,0:08:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To really exist from day to day is,\Nyou know, rags tied together over branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.76,0:08:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And four families live in there\Ntaking turns sleeping on the dirt floor
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.50,0:08:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,while they go about and eat actually more grubs than worms.\NUnbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.83,0:08:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Covered with scabs\Nand the bones all stick out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.52,0:08:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And by age five or six they're dead already.\NOld age almost.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.52,0:09:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In some parts of the world,\NI remember the people are all very small.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.64,0:09:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't much oxygen there anyway,\Nso it's a good thing they're small.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.64,0:09:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only way you can survive there\Nis chewing cocoa leaf
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.64,0:09:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can only work all day long\Nwith nothing to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.84,0:09:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The cocoa leaf, it eliminates your hunger.\NIf you had nothing to eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.87,0:09:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd be stupid not to chew cocoa leaf, wouldn't you?\NOf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.54,0:09:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So this way you can at least survive.\NAnd this little old lady walked by,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.48,0:09:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this little old lady with the ear pads\Nhanging down like this and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.48,0:09:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and they all pad about very quietly like this.\NThe descendants of the Incas,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they live up in the mountains in Peru.\NThe government wants to get them down from there,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.48,0:09:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but they don't want to come down\Nbecause they're smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.48,0:09:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.\NJoin the movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.48,0:09:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Join the big cities in the civilization.\NThis little old crone walks across there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.50,0:09:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said to somebody,\Nhow old is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.79,0:10:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She's 38.\N38, you're an old crone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.79,0:10:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,By 40, you're dead of old age.\NThis one vitamin tablet
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.78,0:10:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,would probably increase her lifespan by 10 years.\NTuberculosis is eating them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't eat because of the cocoa leaf.\NAnd if they do have some money,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.72,0:10:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they spend it on beer.\NAnd there's a red feather hanging out of a shop
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.10,0:10:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,where you can buy beer.\NIt's just a different lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And all that we consider important to them\Nis so irrelevant,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.23,0:10:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't even know what you're talking about.\NYou should all vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.41,0:10:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Vote for what?\NThey're trying to get through
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.41,0:10:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,through till noon,\Nyou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.41,0:10:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Our political system means absolutely nothing to them.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.41,0:10:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of politics is\Nwe're not aware of the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.41,0:10:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people we're talking to.\NSee, the egocentricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.58,0:11:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we're so enamored of our own scheme of things.\NOh, we're so superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.58,0:11:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Superior to what?\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're talking to people,\Nyou have to be aware of their level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.22,0:11:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can speak meaningfully to them.\NSo, a lot of the diplomatic catastrophes of history
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.91,0:11:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,are because of the resumption.\NThat other people are like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.91,0:11:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you folks, they are not like us.\NThey did not go to an Ivy League college.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.91,0:11:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They did not play Marquis of Queensberry rules.\NThey're street people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.91,0:11:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They made you sign a peace treaty with them.\NYou idiot, you turn around and they cut your throat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.01,0:11:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the reason they got you to sign the peace treaty.\NBecause as you leave the table,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.50,0:11:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they got you.\NSucker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.90,0:11:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, those are the realities of the world.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.09,0:11:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to do with the sheep\Nand the wolf in sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.48,0:12:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The vulnerability of the spiritual seeker\Nis that of naivete.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.48,0:12:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially in the beginning years\Nwhere you're enamored of the sudden discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.48,0:12:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of the whole spiritual dimension.\NAnd it's intriguing and it's exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.47,0:12:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that space,\None can go into denial
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.47,0:12:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,about the realities of this world\Nand become a sitting duck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.47,0:12:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I\Nalways counsel these classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.50,0:12:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be a plump little chicken.\NBecause they are out to get you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.84,0:12:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is grace?\NWhat is the function of grace?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.84,0:12:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nwe said that the infinite totality
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.15,0:12:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of creation then\Nradiates these energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.21,0:13:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,To get us out of good and bad\Nand see things as gradations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.39,0:13:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I made up this chart.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.55,0:13:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say up here is preferable\Nand this is less preferable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.62,0:13:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do that.\NPeople say, well, this, this,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.20,0:13:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibration of levels of consciousness\Ncould be used judgmentally.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.51,0:13:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's true.\NIt better be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.63,0:13:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is one thing better than another?\NIt isn't that it's better than another.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.12,0:13:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,From what viewpoint?\NWhen it's cold, heat is preferable to chilly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.67,0:13:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's hot, chilly is preferable to hot.\NSo, from what you choose then,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.72,0:13:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,everything gets rated.\NPeople say, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.23,0:14:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not fair\Nthat things are judged
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.23,0:14:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,one thing better than another.\NI'll tell you a fact about this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.51,0:14:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is better than something else.\NAnd everything is worse than something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.25,0:14:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's all in your head.\NSo, those who object to rating
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.90,0:14:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,people as good or bad or whatever,\Npolitically speaking, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.90,0:14:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are playing a game of pretense,\Nof naivety.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.00,0:14:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, the wolf is hidden\Nin the sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.00,0:14:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's denial of spiritual reality.\NSome things are, frankly,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.20,0:14:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a hell of a lot better than other things.\NNot from an abstract point of view,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.52,0:14:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,no.\NFrom the abstract viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.52,0:14:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you could say that all that exists is equal\Nby virtue of its existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.52,0:14:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't see that\Nuntil you reach calibration level,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.95,0:15:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the top of the deck,\Nuntil you reach a great...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.95,0:15:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In the state of oneness,\Nin the state of the allness of creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.38,0:15:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that all things are equal.\NBut they are equal
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.22,0:15:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different meaning of the term equal\Nthan what is usually
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.60,0:15:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,used in common language.\NIt doesn't mean they are of different value.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.08,0:15:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It means each thing is\Nperfectly that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.60,0:15:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And beauty prevails throughout.\NA stick is equal to a diamond.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.46,0:15:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's of no difference.\NYou see, as you walk through the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.36,0:15:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this weed that stands there.\NOnce you see what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.48,0:15:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,its architecture, its design,\Nis incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.48,0:15:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It stands there in absolute perfection.\NNow you don't call it weed anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.19,0:16:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it as an incredible sculpture.\NThe incredible sculpture of all that exists
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.99,0:16:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is equal to everything else that exists.\NAnd I remember walking down the streets
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.24,0:16:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of New York into the alley\Nand struck by the incredible beauty of the alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.62,0:16:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All the garbage cans and everything.\NIt was like
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.62,0:16:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a French impressionistic painting almost.\NThere was the garbage can
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.62,0:16:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,all dented over like that\Nand the garbage hung out the side
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.62,0:16:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the little mouse ran across\Nand there was the banana peel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.12,0:16:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there is a level in which you see\Nthe beauty and perfection of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.22,0:16:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When that begins to happen,\Nyou tell your friends
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.22,0:16:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're going to the retreat.\NYou're not safe on the streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.35,0:17:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get arrested.\NGrace then is the presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.01,0:17:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the potentiality,\Nthe presence of a very high energy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.01,0:17:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,frequency and vibration\Nwhich through good fortune
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.44,0:17:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,one picks up in one's own aura\Nas an intentionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.07,0:17:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As an intentionality\Nby agreement, by design, by subscription.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd go to see the Karmapa\Nbecause the Karmapa transmits a blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.05,0:17:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,whether he does or doesn't is irrelevant\Nbecause your intention was
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.05,0:17:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach God through every available avenue\Nand even if the Karmapa wasn't there
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.88,0:18:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,he is now by virtue of your intention.\NGrace in a way is the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.58,0:18:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender to that which is intrinsic\Nto salvation and enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.58,0:18:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's walking down the street\Nand suddenly you get
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.02,0:18:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,all you had to do was\Nstart smiling at people
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.02,0:18:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've just transformed the world.\NAnybody can do that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.31,0:18:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,walking down the streets\Nof New York City or Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.31,0:18:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You just start smiling at everybody\Nand instantly everything happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.31,0:18:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It changes.\NIt goes from this world to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.41,0:18:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You did a smile at everybody\Nand everybody goes, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.41,0:18:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the transformative opportunity\Nof a spiritual energy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.01,0:18:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which energizes options\Nthat would perhaps
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.07,0:18:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,not come to mind at the time.\NIn the last lecture we will talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.84,0:18:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an important point\Nin the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.84,0:19:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,where that grace is crucial.\NCrucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.84,0:19:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At that one ten-thousandth of a second\Nthat presence is crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.54,0:19:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you really describe\Nthe physical sensations of the nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.70,0:19:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that you may feel\Nas one progresses in the spiritual path?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.89,0:19:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they can be all kinds of\Nailments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.15,0:19:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of ailments\Nand weird and strange physical sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As one gets really quite advanced\NI think it's because the nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.52,0:19:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is being taxed by this spiritual energy.\NThere is a period of time
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.20,0:19:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's probably in the high five-hundreds.\NWhat I'm thinking about now
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.59,0:19:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the high five-hundreds.\NIt was coming on after six-hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.04,0:20:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was coming on after seven-hundreds.\NIt starts at five-hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.64,0:20:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts at five-forty.\NIt starts at five-fifty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.48,0:20:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts at five-eighty.\NIt starts at five-seventy-five.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.99,0:20:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Five-seventy, five-sixty-five.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.35,0:20:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,At energy level around five-sixty-five\Nwhich would be like saintliness
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.41,0:20:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A Course in Miracles calibrates at six-hundreds.\NIf you do it assiduously
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.79,0:20:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you get transported into that level.\NAnd what is traditionally called the kundalini energy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.40,0:20:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual energy begins to flow of its own.\NI think it's also facilitated by meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.57,0:20:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if it is so.\NThe flow of the kundalini is also facilitated by meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.59,0:21:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Through devotion, worship, spiritual intention\Nand by meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.75,0:21:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this incredible energy begins to flow up your back.\NIt's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.55,0:21:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exquisite.\NBetter than an orgasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.55,0:21:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just beyond imagination.\NIt flows as exquisite, joyful pleasure
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,up the back\Nand you feel it flowing into the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.41,0:21:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you can direct where the energy goes\Nby just sort of focusing your attention
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.41,0:21:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to the left side of the brain\Nto teach the flow over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.41,0:21:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on the right side of the brain.\NIt flows up your back
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.21,0:21:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and into the brain.\NThat's all I can explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.81,0:21:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, you witness this lady hobbling along.\NThis energy flows out intensely
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.81,0:21:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's an exquisite sensation.\NIt flows out, flows in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.81,0:22:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see the lady.\NShe stops hobbling and she walks away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.81,0:22:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens of its own.\NOne is merely the witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.72,0:22:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This energy is what does it.\NThe energy did it for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.88,0:22:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And the\Nirrecoverable, most hopelessly advanced,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.56,0:22:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,serious, psychotic, insane,\Ndegenerated, neurologic,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.56,0:22:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,bizarre creatures would be brought in\Nfrom all over the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.56,0:22:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,wrapped up in wet sheets,\Nsquirming on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.01,0:22:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nlike that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.21,0:22:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And this energy would\Nconnect with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.17,0:22:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the self within the being there\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.61,0:22:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you would feel the inner healing.\NThe inner being was
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.79,0:22:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in the state of peace and grace.\NWhat happened to the physicality
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.89,0:23:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is irrelevant.\NThat's why I tell people
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.75,0:23:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,when you do the Course in Miracles,\Nwhether it cures you or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.75,0:23:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,if the Course is successful,\Nit's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.55,0:23:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the Course takes hold,\Nwhat happens to the physicality
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.55,0:23:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is totally irrelevant.\NIt may or may not heal itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.24,0:23:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If it does, fine.\NIf it doesn't, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.55,0:23:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's irrelevant.\NIt's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.04,0:23:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The kundalini energy is what...\NI mean, I call it kundalini energy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.04,0:23:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's what\NGopi Krishna wrote about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.21,0:23:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like we just\Ndetermined it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.59,0:23:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the high 500s.\NAnd it just is an exquisite state.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.66,0:23:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that state,\Nyou can only see and experience
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.66,0:23:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,love and beauty.\NNothing else exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.66,0:23:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The garbage cans are beautiful.\NEverything...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.98,0:24:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see the architectural,\Nartistic beauty of the garbage cans.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.98,0:24:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see how every weed\Nis perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.58,0:24:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And to this day,\Nit makes no difference to me
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.58,0:24:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,whether a thing is a weed or a diamond.\NNeither one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.79,0:24:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, I don't need either one.\NBut they're equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.41,0:24:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,From that point on,\Nyou don't need anything from this world
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.41,0:24:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or from anyone.\NYou don't need anything from this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.01,0:24:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing that this world has\Nthat has any appeal to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.01,0:24:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why.\NIn the infinite presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.29,0:24:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no lack.\NSo there's no...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.29,0:24:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you would want to reach out for.\NThere's nothing that you want or need.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.88,0:24:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing temptable.\NAnd that's why it's hard to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.31,0:24:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,why some gurus have fallen.\NBecause in that state,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.76,0:24:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing that can appeal to you.\NSo what was appealed to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.79,0:25:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,must have been some remnant.\NSo that kundalini energy then pours in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.32,0:25:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning,\Nthere may be aches and pains.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.64,0:25:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's because the human nervous system\Nis not made for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.64,0:25:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think we calibrated it\Nin a previous meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.73,0:25:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The human nervous system is made\Nfor spiritual energies
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.73,0:25:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrate up to 600.\NAnd beyond that,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.59,0:25:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you should go to other realms.\NGo to other realms.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.59,0:25:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's designed for other realms.\NSo we said homo spiritus
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.92,0:25:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the new emerging advance\Nof homo sapien
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.10,0:25:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the process of developing\Na stronger nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.51,0:25:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that can actually handle\Nmore advanced spiritual energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.51,0:25:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, up to about 600\Nis all that's comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.48,0:26:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's comfortable up to around 700.\NAnd then beyond that,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.54,0:26:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes painful.\NBeyond that, there's,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.64,0:26:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,like the Buddha said,\Nyou're beset by demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.64,0:26:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's aches and pains and fiery,\Nfiery,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.38,0:26:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,fiery,\Nfiery,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.38,0:26:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,fiery.\NI can only liken it to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.38,0:26:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,barbed wire\Nthat's running electricity through it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.38,0:26:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's red hot.\NAnd your whole nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.41,0:26:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes like that\Nand it's agonizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.41,0:26:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And that means\Nthere's something out
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.41,0:26:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've got to find out\Nwhat that is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.66,0:26:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've got to clear that\Nthrough very intense puritano.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.66,0:26:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the human nervous system, then,\Nis made to handle energies
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.66,0:26:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,up to 600,\Nup to 700, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.24,0:26:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And how should we pray?\NWell, we should pray
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.89,0:27:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way we are in the world to respect and have reverence for all of life and the sanctity\Nof all that exists is the epitome of prayer to acknowledge god as the source and the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.38,0:27:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of all existence in all of its expressions is the epitome of prayer people think of\Nprayers in terms of asking for favors oh god i want a mercedes-benz
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.82,0:27:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,she was something else wasn't she when she sang ball and chain the whole audience was just\Nsuspended there's a long pause there in the music and everybody that sits on the edge of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.66,0:27:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,their seats so they stand on their seats and then she finally she comes through with that note and\Nthey all go oh to my mind prayer is not just a recitation see the intention of the recitation
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.93,0:28:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is undoubtedly quite powerful just like prayer reels\Nit's the intention of the prayer reel that gives it its virgin power resist right so whether you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.45,0:28:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,burn sticks uh walk back and forth around the squares and the floor of the cathedral\Nwhatever you do in the name of god for the sake of god is like karma yoga having been done
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.30,0:28:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for the old lord and for the old lord do i thusly peel potatoes back in the floor so for the\Nsake of god i'm going to take some pains of this body write thank you letters send christmas cards
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.31,0:29:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,pay my taxes whatever i do if i do it in the name of god in my because by doing that your\Nyour understanding of the nature of god keeps expanding keeps expanding and that in itself
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.49,0:29:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is a grace to see the opportunity and to follow that opportunity in itself is positive karma\Nis itself grace other people walk through great opportunities and don't see them they're blind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.52,0:29:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can only feel sorry for them that they don't see the great opportunity there\Nwhat is the difference between attachment and detachment well attachment is one of the biggest
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.56,0:29:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,problems in getting rid of the ego and probably the most important one if you can get rid of\Nattachments then you've saved yourself years of spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.35,0:30:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment itself is to some illusion to what you get out of something detachment is uh to say no to\Nit to negate it to refuse it attachment means to be hooked on it detachment would be indifference
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.31,0:30:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,detachment very often is the pathway of no asceticism which is also cool\Nit could be real happy with a cot a box candle and an apple a day
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.42,0:30:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,no money it's easy it's terrific you walk around free as a bird you walk into town somebody says\Nhey my mother just made some donuts you want one all right you walked somebody somebody said you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.55,0:31:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,want to ride somewhere and i said yeah i was thinking going down just everything happens\Nmystically just wonderful don't need anything the downside of asceticism is that one can
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.88,0:31:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,get attached to asceticism you get off you get off on holiness and bone being bony\Nnever taking a shower never washing your hair you can sit there cross-legged this bag of bones
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.25,0:31:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe the you know the ascetics of indiana are the best example\Ni don't know that god's pleased by that or not probably not
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.79,0:31:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm just kidding i've been into asceticism and uh you can get high on asceticism let's say you do\Nyou don't need anything it's fantastic you can walk out of the house without a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.25,0:32:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a nickel, nothing to eat, and everything gets provided day after day. It just happens. The\Nmiraculous becomes constant. Of course, when you're detached, you're not attached to the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.64,0:32:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,survival of life and the body, which can be annoying to your family. They want you to\Ntake care of it and eat and all kinds of strange things, get haircuts, take their medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.79,0:32:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,see the doctor. It's a drag. Anyway, anybody forces you to take all these measures, you\Ndo it because you love them. Frankly, that's why you do it. Left to your own, you wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.34,0:32:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,bother. Left to my own, I wouldn't bother eating. I mean, what would you bother eating\Nfor? I used to not eat for long periods of time, and it would only dawn on me. I hadn't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.78,0:32:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,eaten all week.\NAnd it's like you didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.82,0:32:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,need food. What do you want food\Nfor? The perfect state is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.25,0:33:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,neither attraction nor aversion.\NNeither attachment nor
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.02,0:33:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,detachment necessarily,\Nbut non-attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.70,0:33:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So the present\Nstate is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.85,0:33:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to be not attached. You don't have an aversion\Nnor do you have an attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.23,0:33:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's something for\Ndinner, that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.80,0:33:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there isn't something for dinner, that's also\Ngreat, because you're not attached
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.00,0:33:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,one way or the other.\NNon-attachment. It means you're not run
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.50,0:33:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by it anymore. You're not run by\Nit. And tapas,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.74,0:33:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the traditional way of\NP-A-P-A-S, is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.40,0:33:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the practice of non-attachment to\Nthings. If you always have to have
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.55,0:33:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,your dinner at 5.30,\Nthen you stop doing that until you get over
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.96,0:33:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that yin that it's got to be on the table at\N5.30 or your whole life's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.81,0:34:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be upset.\NWhen you say
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.81,0:34:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,divine intervention is needed,\Nto save us, I hear divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.72,0:34:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,as something other.\NBut there is no other to save
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.23,0:34:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,us from what? Okay.\NDivine intervention
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.59,0:34:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is just a style of speech.\NIt means, out of good
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.82,0:34:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,karma, out of the karma which may\Narise out of the good karma of this instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.40,0:34:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask God to help me.\NCame out of what must be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.96,0:34:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,horrific negative karma, to end\Nup in the depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.63,0:34:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps in that instant was all the karma\Nby grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.34,0:34:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it requires\Nwith the one act,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.19,0:34:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,from here to there. Heaven and hell are a\Ntenth of an inch apart, says Zen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.13,0:35:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely correct.\NAbsolutely correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.61,0:35:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitting bottom may be the\Nfastest way to heaven. That's why
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.71,0:35:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,intervening and\Nbeing an enabler
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.42,0:35:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is interfering with the other person's\Nkarmic lesson. You keep
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.80,0:35:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,running in and saving them and hauling them\Noff to the hospital and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.98,0:35:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,give me a break. The mother used to\Ncall me up. The family called me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.07,0:35:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to stop drinking?\NI said, you know what to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.13,0:35:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Buy him a case of whiskey and put him\Nin a hotel room. Call me back
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.84,0:35:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,when he's done. Right. That's the\Nbest way to help this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.71,0:35:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And when he runs out of a case of whiskey, buy him\Nanother case of whiskey. Pretty soon
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.44,0:35:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the voices are after me, Mom.\NHelp, help. Okay, Junior.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.48,0:35:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we'll take you to the hospital.\NI mean, when you're not ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.19,0:35:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not ready, folks. You know what I mean?\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.32,0:35:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that's it.\NThat's true. Buy him a case of whiskey and leave him
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.42,0:36:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,be. You know, why are you messing with this guy\Nand interfering with his karma?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.42,0:36:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because the good karma\Nonly comes when he surrenders to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.15,0:36:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When he says, God, I've gone\Nas far as I can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.30,0:36:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is a God, I ask him to help me.\NThat stops the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.67,0:36:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,insanity.\NWhen you admit that you, of your own
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.30,0:36:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,nature, you, your little lone\Nego in the middle of the universe, can't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.28,0:36:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,hack it, can't do it.\NThat's truth. That's integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.23,0:36:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nyou cross over the line
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.40,0:36:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of integrity. I, myself,\Ncannot do it. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.80,0:36:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Only by\Ngrace. And you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.03,0:36:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've been insane.\NAnd you ask God to help
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.30,0:36:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you and you surrender your life to God.\NFrom that moment on, your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.26,0:36:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,life is transformed. And this\Nroom is full of people whose lives have been
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.28,0:36:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,transformed in just\Nthat way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.28,0:37:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the grace, then, is that that is\Npresent and available
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.55,0:37:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to you.\NEvery moment. It doesn't mean that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.76,0:37:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be answered at every moment.\NYou can pray up a storm for 20 years
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.40,0:37:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing happens.\NAnd you say, the heck with prayer. I give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.59,0:37:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that instant...\NAnd then you realize you've been
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.63,0:37:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to control God with prayer.\NYou've been trying to control
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.50,0:37:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,him, control. That you weren't\Nreally surrendering. Because if you totally
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.19,0:37:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender to God, it doesn't matter whether the\NRomantism continues or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.71,0:37:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the ailments that you have are really,\Nreally irrelevant, you know, unless
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.07,0:37:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they interfere with functioning. Today, I had to\Nspeak, and all week long, I had some terrible
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.86,0:37:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,virus. Terrible virus.\NAnyway, I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.19,0:37:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,well, either you speak Saturday or you don't speak.\NIf you don't speak, you don't speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.11,0:37:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't speak,\Nyou won't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.82,0:38:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In which case, we'll just sit together and pray, maybe.\NThis asks
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.71,0:38:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,about beings below the 200s.\NWe said, this world seems,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.46,0:38:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,from my personal viewpoint,\Nin fact, you can use the term personal
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.25,0:38:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in its usual vernacular,\Nthe world seems
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.73,0:38:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,purgatorial in design.\NWhy? Because you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.36,0:38:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,go from the very lowest\Nelement, the reptile,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.28,0:38:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the great dinosaurs\Nat 70 lived by
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.61,0:38:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,ravaging and slashing and killing.\NThey live
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.98,0:38:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,solely by the death of others.\NThe dinosaur lives
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.38,0:38:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,only,\Nonly by killing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.76,0:38:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Its sole purpose is to kill\Nyou, because you are food.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.44,0:38:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's about as low as you can get, right?\NI guess worse would be
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.78,0:38:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,kill you and not eat you.\NAt least they eat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.15,0:39:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's starting\Nsomewhere, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.50,0:39:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we get to\Nall we can say is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.26,0:39:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that consciousness evolved\Non this planet. It seemed
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.36,0:39:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to come up from,\Nand there are still beings
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.76,0:39:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bottom of the sea\Nwho are really
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.94,0:39:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,awesomely awesome.\NAnd we see that it evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.30,0:39:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,over great eons of time,\Nmillions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.23,0:39:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,400 million years,\Nfor instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.42,0:39:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we see consciousness\Nslowly come up to where
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.15,0:39:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it has been.\NAnd we see that life
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.42,0:39:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on this earth has been\Na reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.28,0:39:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So life, we said\Nthat the world of form
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.82,0:39:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is the consequence\Nof that which is held
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.21,0:39:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in consciousness.\NThis is a world of effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.90,0:40:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a world of causality.\NIt's a world of effects
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.09,0:40:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in which that which is held\Nin consciousness creates this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.15,0:40:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and then this, and then this,\Nand then this.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.13,0:40:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you walk down the path,\Nyou think it's sequential.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.59,0:40:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not sequential.\NIt's continuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.36,0:40:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is continuous.\NAll things are constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.15,0:40:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the result of an ongoing,\Nongoing creation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.30,0:40:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which is continuous.\NCreation to be creation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.15,0:40:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot start and stop.\NThat which is outside of time
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.44,0:40:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,has no capacity\Nto start and stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.71,0:40:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thusly, everything that is happening\Nis the continuous expression
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.44,0:40:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of creation,\Nthe divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.26,0:40:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite power of God,\Nbringing potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.67,0:40:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,into manifestation.\NAnd consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.86,0:41:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as it evolved then,\Nreached 190,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.59,0:41:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for centuries.\NNow it's at 207,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.25,0:41:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and life has changed.\NDiscuss the Trinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.01,0:41:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,God's Son and Holy Spirit.\NThat's interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.42,0:41:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because it caused the great division\Nof the Christian Church,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.82,0:41:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the Eastern and the Western,\NConstantinople and Rome,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.90,0:41:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,split over this whole concept.\NAnd it has a theological name,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.86,0:41:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what the argument is about.\NThere's three different ways
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.01,0:41:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of looking at things.\NBecause reality is a total,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.01,0:41:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,complete oneness,\Nit cannot have a triune quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.44,0:41:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It can have a triune quality\Nfrom a certain perception,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.80,0:41:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,from a certain level of perception.\NWe see the triune quality
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.01,0:41:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity in the world's religions.\NBrahma, Vishnu, Shiva,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.82,0:42:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we see it in Christianity,\NFather, God, the Son,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.36,0:42:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and God, the Holy Spirit.\NGod, the Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.69,0:42:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and God, the Holy Spirit.\NGod, the Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.94,0:42:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When we say God, the Son,\Nwe're talking about divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.71,0:42:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is expressed in form.\NThat divinity can express itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.21,0:42:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,through the human,\Nthrough the great avatar.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.13,0:42:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that God is invisible\Nto ordinary perception
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.40,0:42:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as that which is transcendent.\NGod is imminent then
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.36,0:42:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,within the avatar.\NAnd what makes it imminent
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.78,0:42:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is the Holy Spirit,\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.61,0:42:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Holy Spirit would be like\Nthe radiance of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.21,0:42:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of God,\Nwhich may then express itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.36,0:42:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,at least to a limited degree,\Nwithin a physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.84,0:42:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the invisible context.\NWhen we pray,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.86,0:43:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what we're referring to,\Nis we've changed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.32,0:43:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the quantum potentiality.\NHow does prayer work?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.30,0:43:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It changes the quantum potentiality.\NIf you follow quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.01,0:43:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that merely to witness\Nor observe a thing already
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.69,0:43:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,changes it.\NThe past and the present
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.17,0:43:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the future change.\NThe future now becomes the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.65,0:43:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the past becomes the future, etc.\NBecause you're out of linearity.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.17,0:43:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind really can't conceive,\Ndoesn't really understand quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.96,0:43:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because only the spiritually evolved person\Ngets what it's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.09,0:43:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are\Nis influenced by the quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.78,0:43:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are is influenced\Nby influencing everything else that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.13,0:43:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,By the virtue of that which you are,\Nyou change the charge and the potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.59,0:44:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore the likelihood\Nof a thing coming into actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.34,0:44:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and form,\Ndepending on local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.76,0:44:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of us then,\Nby their style of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.61,0:44:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by their devotion,\Nby their witness to the acknowledgement
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.50,0:44:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of the sacredness of all of life,\Nlifts the consciousness of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.92,0:44:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All of mankind.\NAll of mankind is benefited.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.90,0:44:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing goes unobserved.\NNot a hair on your head
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.63,0:44:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,shall be missed.\NThat turned out to be accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.09,0:44:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when I first discovered\Nthe capacity of kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.82,0:44:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell truth from falsehood.\NAnd I realized that everything that ever existed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.51,0:44:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is registered forever\Nin the field of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.15,0:44:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, whoa.\NEvery hair on your head
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.78,0:44:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,shall be counted.\NWhoa. It's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.67,0:44:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact. Every squirrel that falls,\Nis noted.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.73,0:45:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Intrinsic divinitive existence\Nis equal in all.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.46,0:45:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is equal in all.\NWitnessed, acknowledged by all.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.65,0:45:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When we say God imminent,\NGod transcendent,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.23,0:45:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when we talk about Trinity,\NGod, Son, Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.78,0:45:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,those are only linguistic,\Nconceptual,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.48,0:45:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,rationalistic positionalities\Nfrom which to approach the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.05,0:45:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When you read,\Ntheology, realize
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.94,0:45:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,what a difficult job that is\Nto try to describe the non-linear
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.01,0:45:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in terms that are linear.\NTo describe that which is indefinable.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.76,0:45:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how you can define the indefinable.\NThat's what theology is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.65,0:45:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Class, we will define the indefinable.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.92,0:45:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see the difficulty.\NHowever, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.71,0:46:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you can also see the\Ndevotion in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.61,0:46:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, many of the great intellectual,\Nspiritual teachers of history,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.05,0:46:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in the religious thing,\Nwere very learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.59,0:46:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They were doctors of theology.\NTheir devotion was to the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.17,0:46:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and it took the form of a seeking truth\Nthrough the intellect and reason and logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.65,0:46:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one can still be respectful of the devotion\Nbehind the endeavor to try to reach,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.40,0:46:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nif you read about the books,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.09,0:46:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, it'll discuss whether God is imminent or transcendent.\NWell, this is an artifact of mentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.55,0:46:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It couldn't possibly be either or.\NGod being the essence of all that exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.67,0:46:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the allness throughout and beyond all time,\Ncould hardly be limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.94,0:47:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,could hardly be divided into transcendent,\Nwhich is out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.78,0:47:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and imminent, which is in here.\NThose are obviously just artifacts of human mentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.09,0:47:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We've sort of touched upon prayer.\NWe need the Newtonian versus the,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.55,0:47:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to put it within conceptual basis,\NI don't want to spend much time at this,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.19,0:47:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's worth,\Nfor the doubting Thomas,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.36,0:47:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,there are people who are stuck in their intellect,\Nand victims of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.42,0:47:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't get out of my brain, dog.\NCan't get out of logic, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.80,0:47:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you can't.\NBut God in his infinite mercy knows that,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.88,0:47:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are stuck in your head.\NFor those who are stuck in their head then,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.69,0:48:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay to be spiritual\Nbecause we now have a scientific explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.84,0:48:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for the reality of the spiritual.\NThis is the Newtonian paradigm of reality on the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.25,0:48:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in which things are discrete, orderly, logical,\Ndefinable, measurable,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.25,0:48:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's what the material reductionist,\Nthe hardcore scientist says is what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.25,0:48:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't measure it.\NYou can't weigh it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.25,0:48:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't locate it in time and space.\NIt's not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.25,0:48:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sort of taking great liberties with the word real.\NIn fact, it's really missing what real is about,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.07,0:48:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but anyway, that's beside the point.\NSo this is the world that we presume to be reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.28,0:48:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,except that actually we don't\Nbecause nobody lives on that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.30,0:48:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We entertain ourselves with that level,\Nbut we all know we live on the experiential,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.30,0:48:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,either like the plum pudding or you don't.\NGot too much this in it or too much that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.46,0:49:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The liver is fried too hard\Nand it's tough as leather or it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.46,0:49:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NSo this is where we live over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.92,0:49:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We live in the infinite quantum potentiality.\NYou know, as we get smaller and smaller
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.98,0:49:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,below the atom, below the sub-particles,\Nsub-particle physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.98,0:49:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we get to like potentiality.\NLike potential energies that are so minute
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.40,0:49:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that they cannot be measured.\NAnd we enter a different realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.00,0:49:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We enter a different realm.\NWe enter the world where we live.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.73,0:49:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we live is in spirituality.\NPeople say, I don't believe in spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.92,0:49:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot, you live there all day long.\NIn fact, what just said you don't live in spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.92,0:49:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is what spirituality is.\NIt's a subjective conclusion
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.01,0:49:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and how did that come about?\NIt's the totality of all one's thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.01,0:50:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time,\None's karmic inheritance
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.01,0:50:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and what your consciousness level is now\Nthat leads you to feel that way within yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.23,0:50:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that gives it that sense of truth\Nthat you say this is so highly complex,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.23,0:50:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,completely non-linear.\NSo where we live is really disorderly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.96,0:50:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything can happen within your experiential life.\NYou can go to your favorite opera
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.96,0:50:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and be disappointed instead of ecstatic.\NYou can buy your best ice cream
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.96,0:50:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've always liked your whole life\Nand you decide it's disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.96,0:50:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really predict what's going to happen.\NIt's creative. It's free.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.09,0:50:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's imaginative. It's progressive.\NIt's diffuse. It's non-local.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.67,0:50:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's experiential.\NIt's expansive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.96,0:50:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the context out of which we live.\NIt's the subjective state.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.25,0:50:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And at all times we're really poised\Nfor the next instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.28,0:51:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The context of our life then is unlimited.\NAt every moment we're poised for the next instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.28,0:51:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Without even being conscious and aware that we're poised,\Nat every instant everybody here is ready to jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.57,0:51:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That jumping-ness can happen out of non-jumping-ness.\NNothing said jump in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.32,0:51:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It just jumped. See?\NSo everything is happening spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.55,0:51:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as an expression of the essence of...\Nthe reality of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.61,0:51:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This entire lecture was prepared exactly\None ten-thousandth of a second ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.26,0:51:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jump wasn't in it. You know what I mean?\NHere's some things about the downside of social life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.30,0:52:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside of social life.\NThere are those things which are preferable
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.23,0:52:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and those things which are not preferable.\NSee, if we can get beyond good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.30,0:52:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we can say there's the things that we want\Nand we call them good.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.36,0:52:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's the things we don't want\Nand we call them bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.26,0:52:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here we've got, which we had before\Nbut we didn't talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.30,0:52:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,See, good and bad, just like talking about the Trinity,\Ndepends on where you want to start from.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.30,0:52:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you're talking about is the perception\Nand what you're talking about is the point
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.30,0:52:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from which you're approaching the subject.\NIf you desire it, you say it's good,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.96,0:52:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't desire it, you say it's bad.\NSo the things that we consider tragic about society,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.15,0:52:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,about human life,\Nwar and the downside of the judiciary system,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.15,0:53:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, there is a downside to it,\Nare because we don't want those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.57,0:53:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So we choose what we want\Nand we repel that which we don't want.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.71,0:53:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In the highest state, they're all the same,\Nas we said.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.71,0:53:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,War and peace, it's all the same.\NWhether you all go off with an atomic bomb, bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.71,0:53:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or you slowly strangle to death from old age,\Nwhat's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.71,0:53:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you're going to leave here quick and easy\Nor slow and horrible, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.42,0:53:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving is leaving.\NAnd whatever karmic merit there is
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.42,0:53:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the style that's chosen,\Nbut that's a very advanced state.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.03,0:53:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is a certain level at which you can see\Nthat it really doesn't matter
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.32,0:53:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because this being a karmic theater,\Nthis being a theater of great opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.32,0:54:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then we can choose that which we choose\Nand not choose that which we mean to avoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.32,0:54:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself wouldn't want the karma\Nof being a judge in a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.55,0:54:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you.\NI wouldn't want the karma
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.30,0:54:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of being the one that says,\Nthis person dies or doesn't die or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.67,0:54:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think the difficulty with leading a moral\Nor an ethical or spiritual life in the West,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.90,0:54:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Western world,\Nis the lack of the understanding of karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.90,0:54:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the lack of the understanding of the nature of God,\Nthat everything and every moment
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.23,0:54:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,determines one's spiritual destiny.\NThat everything, every moment
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.46,0:54:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is an act that is witnessed by the entire universe.\NThe entire universe witnesses every single act
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.46,0:54:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and every single choice\Nand records it forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.98,0:55:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, in the demonstrations we do of kinesiology\Nand the potentiality of it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.36,0:55:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as a research tool,\Nwe go back in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.67,0:55:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,any human being that ever lived,\Nwhat they thought or felt,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.67,0:55:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what they did,\Nwhy they made the choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.67,0:55:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is hidden.\NNothing is hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.48,0:55:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So from the infinite eye of the divine,\Nnothing is hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.90,0:55:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,\Nneither does it need to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.44,0:55:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the blessing.\NSo we'll break for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.44,0:57:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see you again later.\NAbout an hour or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.40,0:57:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it.\NBe able to function
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.36,0:57:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in the presence of the beauty of God\Nis difficult and takes practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.03,0:57:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And by Lecture 11,\NI've made good progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.86,0:58:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It used to be\NI could either deal with the music
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.86,0:58:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or talk, but not both.\NHow to not be wiped out by it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.86,0:58:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Question number one.\NIs it the mind-boggler of all time?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.46,0:58:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,How does one truly find themself?\NWell, it's a snap, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.44,0:58:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You just realize you're the infinite allness\Nof all existence beyond all time and expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.44,0:58:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are.\NDidn't take long, did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.76,0:58:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,After many lifetimes,\NI got a neat letter from somebody the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.32,0:58:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He says,\NI've been meditating for 30 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.17,0:59:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly,\Nboom.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.09,0:59:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How neat.\NThere's questions about prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.59,0:59:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's questions about meditation.\NWonderful questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.88,0:59:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that the ultimate form of prayer\Nis the way in which you conceptualize,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.55,0:59:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the way in which you contextualize\Nyour own existence from instant to instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.55,0:59:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation and prayer\Nis more like a mudra
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.32,0:59:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,than a recitation.\NIt's more like a posture
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.80,0:59:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you pose your existence\Nin the context of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.00,1:00:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the style in which you are\Nout of the awareness of the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.69,1:00:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and once surrendered to be of service to God.\NThat sanctifies all actions.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.11,1:00:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It is by your dedication of yourself\Nto that intention
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.86,1:00:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that you sanctify all your actions.\NThat's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.61,1:00:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the last thing,\Nthe last thing that I want to do
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.61,1:00:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is ask you a question\Nthat I must ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.61,1:00:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it from you\Nto do with your action?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.03,1:00:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your action?\NDo you have an action?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.61,1:00:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the action you do\Nto help you relax?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.07,1:00:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NActually,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.25,1:00:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to give you\Na few different answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.59,1:01:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a strange question.\NIt really is.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.59,1:01:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know\Nif it's the same or a different answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.86,1:01:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is.\NIf I do something wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.86,1:01:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that person\NThere's a sense of wholesomeness about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.92,1:01:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's made by a machine, there's certain brands of bread\Nthat you could blindfold me,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.40,1:01:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the minute you put it in your mouth, it tastes dead.\NTwinkies. I'm very disappointed in Twinkies.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.88,1:01:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, Twinkies came to mind.\NWhen I was a kid, you'd go out for, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.23,1:01:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,your mom would put a Twinkie in there,\Nand at lunch you'd have your Twinkie,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.80,1:01:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'd squeeze that banana-flavored goodness out of it.\NTwinkies were great.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.75,1:01:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, out of madness, I decided to buy a Twinkie for old-time's sake.\NMan, it was deader than a mackerel.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.80,1:01:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it is not the same Twinkie that I grew up with.\NFood that is blessed carries a different energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.11,1:02:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so the human energy does something to the energy of the food itself.\NSo witness the mother who lovingly makes the chicken soup.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.21,1:02:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It actually does cure your cold.\NAnd the tea that's made it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.76,1:02:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tea that's made it home has cured this cold.\NIt's because of the energy of love within it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.94,1:02:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So we transform everything that we touch.\NWe know that people who have a green thumb, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.63,1:02:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like they see the sacredness of beauty.\NThey dedicate their life to the cultivation of beauty for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.13,1:02:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We sanctify that which we do then by the dedication of our life\Nto be conscious that all one's actions are in the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.80,1:02:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and that every action is in the presence of God.\NAnd that every action affects all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.73,1:02:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So your life no longer is trivial.\NYour life is no longer trivial.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.00,1:03:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you're out on a river fishing,\Nas you look over and you appreciate the beauty of that river and the surroundings,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.38,1:03:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,your appreciation of that beauty is radiating out and lifting all of mankind.\NSo even as you sit in the rowboat thinking that you're doing nothing,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.53,1:03:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,your acknowledgement of the beauty of creation itself\Nis an act of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.23,1:03:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an act of sanctifying all of life\Nand affirming its value and increasing its value.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.38,1:03:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how the consciousness level of mankind evolves\Nis because those who are more conscious tend to lift all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.73,1:03:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that the top of the levels of consciousness are numerically small,\Nbut their power outweighs...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.94,1:04:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but their power outweighs all the rest of the population.\NOne person who dedicates themself to life
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.92,1:04:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and sees the sacredness of all of life\Nand thereby sanctifies all of life as they go about the day
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.80,1:04:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is lifting the consciousness of thousands of other people.\NSomewhere in Biatra, some little kid is laying there,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.21,1:04:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly dying of starvation and AIDS.\NAnd out of his hopelessness and grief and apathy,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.05,1:04:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly there's a little spark of hope.\NAnd death is okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.19,1:04:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did that come from?\NIt came from the fisherman sitting there appreciating the beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.09,1:04:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because the context of life is non-linear,\Nso in the infinite quantum potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.38,1:04:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,every intention on your part alters the context for everyone.\NEvery hair on your head is counted.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.28,1:05:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Every moment of your life contributes this way\Nor it pulls it down this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.90,1:05:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of people who are living in this world,\Nthe number of people who are living in this world,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.92,1:05:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of people who calibrate on the high levels\Nhas increased since 1980, 1990, whatever it was,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.01,1:05:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,1990s when I did it, early 1990s.\NAnd the calibration of the level of all of mankind is going up.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.30,1:05:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see, as we said, at 207, integrity no longer,\Npeople don't wink at it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.03,1:05:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They put it on the front cover of Fortune magazine.\NIntegrity is being called for by everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.09,1:05:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you say to God\Nwhen you pray?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.01,1:05:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what other people say to God when they pray.\NI could use a few more bucks, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.11,1:05:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Rent's due next week.\NI mean, I'm sure God doesn't take offense at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.28,1:06:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really a serious question of how does one pray.\NThe most effective prayer, as far as I know, is non-verbal.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.86,1:06:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It is to position oneself.\NYou know what a mudra is?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.50,1:06:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A mudra is...\NYou see, divine statues.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.07,1:06:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A mudra is this.\NMudra is the dance of Shiva.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.55,1:06:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mudra is a posture.\NA mudra is blessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.73,1:06:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mudra is...\NSo it's one's...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.59,1:06:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you position your existence vis-a-vis divinity.\NIt's like there's an...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.53,1:06:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you picture an invisible self,\Nwhat would be the posture of your invisible self?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.75,1:06:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess...\NProbably...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.44,1:07:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in the presence of God.\NThat's how.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.05,1:07:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask.\NWe have permission to ask about that
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.15,1:07:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,form of prayer resist.\NIt's more effective than
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.09,1:07:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,verbalization resist.\NMore effective than verbalization.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.36,1:07:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a supplication of your spirit\Nto God's will.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.69,1:07:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The surrender to God's will\Nis a form of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.88,1:07:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When you say,\Nfor what reason I don't know, Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.67,1:07:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but I, whatever,\Nin thy name, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.01,1:07:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's the undoing of some bad karma,\Nyou might say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.05,1:07:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the reason for this suffering is,\Nbut I dedicate it for, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.90,1:07:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the undoing of whatever karma\Nit may be undoing, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.42,1:07:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to have everything\Nsubserve the good of all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.67,1:08:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The next question is about meditation.\NI've got them backwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.92,1:08:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder I can't read.\NAs you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.43,1:08:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to hold your existence\Nin a certain,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.31,1:08:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it's almost like a benediction.\NIt's almost like
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.43,1:08:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sanctifying one's own existence\Nby your posture vis-a-vis God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.56,1:09:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as sitting meditation,\Nso this, in a way, is a meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.84,1:09:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a way of being in the world\Nin which one,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.85,1:09:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as everything arises,\None surrenders it to God
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.07,1:09:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because to avoid\Nattractions and aversions,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.57,1:09:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,then one becomes detached\Nand one surrenders
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.36,1:09:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all possibility to God.\NIf this happens,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.65,1:09:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll go bankrupt.\NWell, if I go bankrupt,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.06,1:09:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I go bankrupt.\NLots of people survive bankruptcy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.07,1:09:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They still tend to be breathing and eating.\NIf that's what it takes,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.13,1:09:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if that's what it takes\Nto get off materiality,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.55,1:09:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to get off pride of advantage,\Nto get off the vanity of materialism,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.31,1:09:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then I guess if it takes bankruptcy to do it,\Nso let it be.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.94,1:10:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Bankruptcy is one of the ways to God.\NAfter you get rid of all the money
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.63,1:10:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the big cars\Nand all the crap,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.93,1:10:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you say,\NI'm still me
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.40,1:10:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and I still enjoy fishing\Nand life hasn't really changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.55,1:10:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NBecause love remains.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.34,1:10:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Love.\NThere is formal meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.28,1:10:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's meditation as a lifestyle.\NSo what I just described to you
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.40,1:10:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,was meditation as a mudra,\Nas a lifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.05,1:10:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which is itself a meditation.\NContemplation would be the next
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.17,1:10:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,more focused level\Nin which one is aware
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.18,1:10:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of the rising and the falling away\Nof the feelings, thoughts, and events
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.01,1:10:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as they occur.\NThe focus is on that which is a priority.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.76,1:10:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is just before the arising,\Njust before the arising of the thought and the feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.02,1:11:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then let go wanting to change it.\NLet go resisting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.59,1:11:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And it rises, it crests,\Nand then it falls away
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.31,1:11:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,with no commentary.\NThat's a complete surrender to God
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.61,1:11:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in the everyday activities.\NSo you dedicate your life to God
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.21,1:11:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way in which you are with the world,\Nwith the dedication,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.52,1:11:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,with the reverence\Nwith which you do everything
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.53,1:11:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,from digging a ditch\Nto peeling a potato
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.72,1:11:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to making dinner.\NIt's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.22,1:11:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the same.\NBut it makes a difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.27,1:11:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The potato that's fueled by love\Nand cooked with love
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.09,1:11:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is a different potato\Nthan one that is chopped up by a machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.71,1:11:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NAnybody can check it out for themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.07,1:12:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,More formal sitting meditation,\Na la Zen,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.82,1:12:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is a more disciplined,\Nconscious, focused, concentrated,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.39,1:12:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,time-out from life\Nin which the focus can be
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.15,1:12:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a one-pointedness of mind\Non the thoughts as they arise.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.19,1:12:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this condition,\None becomes,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.10,1:12:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,one transcends from the experience.\NWe have a chart that shows it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.68,1:12:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We showed it before.\NYou transcend identification
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.63,1:12:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with the thoughts\Nand you become that which witnesses the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.97,1:12:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.\NWell, these are really,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.31,1:13:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,really the levels of consciousness\Nthat strict meditation will take you through.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.10,1:13:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Strict meditation,\Nthe mentation goes on and on.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.86,1:13:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can stop the mentation.\NThe mentation proliferates faster
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.35,1:13:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,than you can counter it.\NSo therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.35,1:13:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,one has to transcend\Nto become that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.00,1:13:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing the mentation as it goes by.\NThe memories,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.39,1:13:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the fantasies,\Nthe daydreams,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.89,1:13:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,little bits of music,\Nibbity-dibbity,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.39,1:13:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,boom,\Nheady-fishies in an itty-bitty bowl,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.15,1:13:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all this crap goes through your head.\NYou can't stop it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.38,1:13:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\NHitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.27,1:13:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the third world war,\NI mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.52,1:13:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,all the wars,\Neverything goes through your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.60,1:13:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Little bits from childhood,\Nlittle pieces of music,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.18,1:13:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,some vignette from a television commercial,\NBow Flux commercial.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.93,1:13:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I posed for that years ago\Nand they're still using it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.35,1:14:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They asked me to do\Na geriatric version of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.69,1:14:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In which you only lose five pounds,\Nnot 400 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.84,1:14:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Five pounds will do.\NSo at first you're preoccupied with form
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.64,1:14:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to see that\Nas we tried to stop your thoughts before,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.07,1:14:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they won't stop.\NThey won't stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.93,1:14:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Something is registering those thoughts\Nand recognizing them
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.52,1:14:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and you realize,\Nthat that within you is,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.06,1:14:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,while thoughts and all this is going on,\Nsomething is witnessing them.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.36,1:14:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You say,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.60,1:14:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,George,\NI'm thinking about so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.51,1:14:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows or what is it\Nthat knows what you're thinking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.72,1:14:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's something beyond the thinkingness\Nthat is the witness of the thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.02,1:15:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So you let go identifying with the thoughts.\NI mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.21,1:15:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't be the thoughts.\NIf you were the thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.14,1:15:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,when you told them to stop,\Nthey'd stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.93,1:15:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nno,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.85,1:15:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the victim of the thoughts.\NYou're the victim of the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.15,1:15:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it that's the victim of the thoughts?\NThe watcher,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.10,1:15:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer.\NHow do you know
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.32,1:15:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that this watcher or experiencer\Ncan report what it's reporting?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.28,1:15:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because there's a quality\Nand what we're looking for is a quality.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.71,1:15:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A non-personal quality\Nof awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.98,1:15:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the observer and the witness.\NSo in meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.22,1:15:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you're trying to sense.\NWhat is it that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.50,1:15:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,prior to the thought?\NWhat is it that the thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.85,1:15:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,how is it that they register?\NThere is within, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.69,1:16:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a quality to the consciousness.\NThe quality of consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.42,1:16:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which itself is silent.\NIt's because of the silence,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.92,1:16:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the background silence,\Nthat you can hear sound.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.27,1:16:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right,\Nyou can focus either on the sound
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.52,1:16:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or the silence that makes detecting\Nthe sound possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.81,1:16:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Similarly,\Nyou can focus on consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.84,1:16:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which itself is without form,\Nbut which illuminates all form.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.02,1:16:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begin to withdraw from the thoughts.\NThe thoughts are changing all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.81,1:16:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't be who you are.\NYou would have been dead a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.39,1:16:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So one withdraws one's identification\Nto the more detached.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.93,1:16:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We use the analogy also\Nof content versus context.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.51,1:16:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The thoughts themselves\Nare the content.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.26,1:16:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But what is the overall context\Nwhich is holding this capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.92,1:17:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for thought and feeling and all\Nin the first place?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.68,1:17:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is a priority?\NWhat is more prior?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.18,1:17:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You go through the whole story\Nof your job with so-and-so
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.81,1:17:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they screwed you\Nand didn't give you the raise you would do.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.68,1:17:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So you go through these stories,\Nlaments from the past,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.97,1:17:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or daydreams of the future,\Nbut they're all stories.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.14,1:17:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the willingness to surrender\Nthe storiness of this recollection to God
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.56,1:17:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to shorten it.\NLetting go of the wanting to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.36,1:17:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll find that thinking\Nis coming out of a wanting to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.27,1:17:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a desire to think.\NFirst of all,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.31,1:17:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we think thoughts are wonderful.\NThe reason we think they're wonderful
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.68,1:17:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is because they're our thoughts.\NSomebody else's thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.82,1:17:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,are not really all that charming\Nwhen you think of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.22,1:17:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, would you like to hear\Nwhat I think?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.53,1:18:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think about now?\NOkay, so we're enamored of thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.56,1:18:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're our thoughts.\NIf they're our thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.27,1:18:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they're wonderful, precious, and valuable.\NIf they're somebody else's thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.44,1:18:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they're stupid.\NSo we get to the core of thinking this,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.40,1:18:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the narcissistic,\Negocentric investment in them.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.17,1:18:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thoughts are wonderful, valuable,\Nand valid
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.32,1:18:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're ours.\NMy thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.15,1:18:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you get off that,\Nis you realize that thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.02,1:18:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is happening of itself.\NThey aren't your thoughts at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.53,1:18:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As you look at the energy fields of consciousness,\Nthere are huge thought fields
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.76,1:18:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in which your consciousness is immersed.\NAnd the thinkingness of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.30,1:18:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is what's programming your head,\Ntogether with last night's TV news, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.61,1:18:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We get off the vanity.\NSo there's a secret vanity
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.73,1:19:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to the thinkingness.\NThe thinkingness also brings us back to the thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.88,1:19:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings up a feelingness.\NAnd you'll notice that all thinkingness has a payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.35,1:19:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting one up on something.\NYou're getting even with something.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.97,1:19:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think negative thoughts about people,\Nsecretly you're punishing them.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.14,1:19:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That crazy old bitch.\NThat nutty old man.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.11,1:19:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He deserves arthritis.\NWe get a secret getting even kind of feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.56,1:19:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We write wrongs.\NWe write these wonderful stories in our head.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.50,1:19:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How we write these wrongs.\NHow the guilty are made to pay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.80,1:19:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right.\NYou see, this thinkingness happens
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.07,1:20:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's a desire to think.\NBecause there's a secret payoff to thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.48,1:20:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we think that thinkingness is valuable.\NIt's coming from an energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.71,1:20:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a root to thinkingness.\NAs you let go,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.93,1:20:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting to dramatize\Neverything into the form of thinkingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.69,1:20:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,into the form of a story,\Nyou'll see the self-indulgence of that
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.31,1:20:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and the egocentricity if you look at it.\NAs your head manufactures these stories,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.56,1:20:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's strictly egocentric.\NIt's strictly narcissistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.06,1:20:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very self-indulgent.\NYou see that the ego is in love with itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.39,1:20:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting an enormous payoff\Nfrom all this thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.52,1:20:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You decide to turn the pleasure,\Nthe secret pleasure of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.35,1:20:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,over and surrender it to God.\NAs you let go,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.97,1:21:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting to make stories,\Nthey become paragraphs.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.14,1:21:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As you let go,\Nwanting to write paragraphs,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.17,1:21:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they become short sentences.\NAnd then you begin to see
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.06,1:21:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the unloggy of thoughts as they arise.\NIt's like there's a primordial energy bed
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.72,1:21:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not yet into form.\NIt wants to come into form.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.53,1:21:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts to think dog.\NThen it thinks about old Bawa,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.47,1:21:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and you remember how old Bawa was sick.\NYou remember how Bawa used to bring the paper in.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.38,1:21:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember how the kids used to play with Bawa.\NAnd there's a whole story about Bawa.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.97,1:21:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty soon you're weeping\Nthinking about when Bawa died.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.46,1:21:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, I mean, it just grows, right?\NAll right, so there has to be a willingness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.77,1:21:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender all that.\NThe sentimentality,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.38,1:21:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the validation of yourself\Nas the good pet owner or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.68,1:21:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go of the sadness\Nof the thinking of the good old days, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.39,1:22:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the long story about Bawa\Nborrows down to a paragraph,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.89,1:22:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,then it comes down to a sentence.\NThen you catch the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.38,1:22:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,starting to think about Bawa,\Nand you surrender it at that point.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.57,1:22:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a constant surrenderingness.\NAs you do this,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.67,1:22:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is you nip thoughts in the bud.\NYou'll see they're coming out
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.82,1:22:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of a formless unloggy,\Nfree form, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.06,1:22:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't quite dogginess yet.\NAnd the word dog doesn't exist yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.30,1:22:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But image of dogginess,\Nall this happens very rapidly,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.11,1:22:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's continuous.\NSo there's like a continuous fount
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.46,1:22:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinkingness coming out of a\Nenergy field that we could just call
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.52,1:22:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness,\Nthe energy like a fountain
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.14,1:22:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which proliferates\Nthinkingness endlessly.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.02,1:22:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One surrenders this to God\Nat greater and greater depth
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.14,1:22:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,until finally one gets to the very core\Nof thinkingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.64,1:23:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And one surrenders\Nthe identification of self
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.88,1:23:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as thinkingness\Nand surrenders thinkingness to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.10,1:23:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That is quite a sacrifice.\NWould you be willing to become
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.72,1:23:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a dumb animal who doesn't think?\NYou can become a happy dog,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.52,1:23:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not going to be able\Nto think again.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.00,1:23:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be a happy purring kitty,\Nbut you won't be allowed
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.65,1:23:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to think anymore.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.36,1:23:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't think if I'm a kitty?\NYou can purr.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.40,1:23:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.\NI can't think anymore, God?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.35,1:24:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be a kitty.\NBecause the identification of self
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.76,1:24:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is thinkingness is part and parcel\Nof identifying yourself as ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.72,1:24:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as human ego.\NAnd you'll see the great reluctance
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.15,1:24:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with which you let go\Nand the tenacity with which you let
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.26,1:24:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,hang on to thinkingness\Ndespite your lamenting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.30,1:24:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody laments their thoughts.\NI was laying in bed
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.68,1:24:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and I couldn't go to sleep.\NI kept coming back and back.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.11,1:24:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody laments their thoughts.\NIf you really lamented your thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.96,1:24:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they would stop.\NSo you think you're lamenting your thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.88,1:24:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're secretly delighting\Nin their torment.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.35,1:24:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to give up\Nthe secret delight in the torment.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.19,1:24:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So in really intense meditation then,\Nthere is a willingness
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.65,1:24:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender everything to God.\NThinkingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.40,1:24:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you end up surrendering\Nis mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.94,1:24:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to surrender mind,\Nmind.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.27,1:25:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Itself to God.\NThen you discover
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.36,1:25:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there isn't such a thing as mind anyway.\NThere's only thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.02,1:25:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only thoughts.\NAnd as thoughts disappear,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.10,1:25:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so does mind.\NThere's no such thing as mind
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.56,1:25:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,any more than there is such a thing as ego.\NBut for spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.14,1:25:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we call the ego the ego\Nat least for a period of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.02,1:25:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we reach a certain level\Nwhere we realize there is no such structure
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.64,1:25:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and only our belief systems\Nwork.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.52,1:25:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we start holding it in place\Nand that it is not really an it at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.52,1:25:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have any independent existence.\NFormal sitting meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.65,1:25:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is in itself an end.\NAnd many people have spent
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.65,1:25:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,many a lifetime,\Nmany years in a strict meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.89,1:25:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself spent\NI don't know how many lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.89,1:26:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in meditation.\NIt is, of course, classically
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.52,1:26:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the way of non-duality,\Nthe royal road to God through non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.52,1:26:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The quote is,\Nthe core is Zen practice,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.93,1:26:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and many other practices,\Nnot just Zen.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.56,1:26:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Any one of the meditative practices\Ncan bring you into various levels of satori.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.42,1:26:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,These levels of satori\Nare sudden flashes where you transcend mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.82,1:26:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ambiguities are resolved\Nbecause you see the positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.82,1:26:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that was creating the apparent opposites\Nand they suddenly collapse.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.82,1:26:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nso meditation itself
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.78,1:26:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is certainly a worthy endeavor.\NOne's dedication of meditation to God
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.27,1:26:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of looking for a benefit.\NSo the other block to get out of the way
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.61,1:27:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is to stop meditating for something.\NOne cannot meditate in order to reach satori,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.93,1:27:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to reach enlightenment,\Nin order to realize one's Buddha nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.93,1:27:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,One meditates for the sake of meditation\Nperiod.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.93,1:27:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because it will get you anything,\Nget you anywhere,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.93,1:27:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not for any alleged or imagined gain.\NThat is a sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.02,1:27:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To sacrifice all goal.\NI meditate
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.18,1:27:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,out of devotion to Thee, O Lord.\NPeriod.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.07,1:27:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Formal sitting meditation can last.\NI did it for 20 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.07,1:27:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,an hour in the morning,\Nan hour at night.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.07,1:27:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When you had more time,\NI used to meditate six hours a day
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.10,1:27:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or eight hours a day\Nand then I went into
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.10,1:27:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,24 hour day meditation.\NSince then I haven't meditated at all.
